    "Management": {
      "text": "PO\nanalgesia\nCycloplegics\nparalyze the ciliary body resulting in a nonreactive and dilated pupil, preventing synechiae, progression of flare, ciliary spasm pain\n[6]\nHomatropine\n5% BID-TID\nCyclopentolate\n2% TID\nScopolamine\n0.25% BID\nTopical steroids\nin consult with optho\nRule out infection first and avoid corneal epithelial defect\nPrednisolone\nacetate 0.5-1% QID\nIf secondary\nglaucoma\nas complication, may use\ntimolol\n0.5% BID if no contraindication",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
